text: Going by this trailer this movie seems like it may be one to see. JLo , KeKe, and Cardi who? Cardi (B)utterflie . I love Jennifer Lopez work ethic. I will say it again. I don't think she is the best singer, dancer or actor but that work ethic  is it. Another valuable thing about her that I really like is: Jennifer Lopez is very successful in the music and entertainment industry I really, really like that she gives more than the price of admission to her supporters. I don't like to say fans. Since making it in the industry she has never stopped giving time to the late night talk shows, she will do the morning talk shows, she will do radio interviews. At the recent power outage in New York she took time to speak about it and voice regret about having to cancel and inconvenience  those who were there for Her show and it wasn't even her fault that the power outage happened. I want to believe that she understands that those in attendance for her show do not have to pay their money to come out to see her. She recognize that they can spend their money elsewhere but choose to pay it to see her. She gives more than the price of admission . She gives more and I really like that about this woman. A successful person like her with a channel on the Tube letting folks into even more of her regular ole' superstar status life. Not a lot of people in her designer shoes would even think or ever think about having a channel on the Tube.  I don't know her and will probably never ever meet her but I really like that about her. I think that's why God keeps blessing her with more and more.  She takes time out of her big huge life to at 'least' let her followers hear her speaking voice and not always her singing voice. I'll let those reading this figure that one out.  Bye Everybody, Take Care of each other.  I apologize for the length of this. I had something to say is all.  17 July 2019     02:14
